ical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","type":"topic","title":"MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointFeature":{"title":"MLNPointFeature","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointFeature","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointFeature","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointFeature","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object associates a point shape with an optional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier and attributes."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointfeature","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNFeature":{"title":"MLNFeature","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"  protocol is used to provide details about geographic features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contained in an "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object. Each concrete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subclass of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" in turn has a subclass that conforms to this protocol. A"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"feature object associates a shape with an optional identifier and attributes."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnfeature","fragments":[{"text":"MLNFeature","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNAnnotationView","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"reference"},{"text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView",